function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)

	--Play Phase 2 Victory Stinger
	Hydra.MusicOverride("CSD_Kehj_Hell_ThroneOfHatred", "Music_Boss_Lilith_Phase2_Victory")

	-- TEMP - this should be spawned on her ash pile!
	idFirstTimeRewardLocation = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(sFirstTimeRewardDropActor, idActorKilled)
	
	Hydra.BossEncounterManuallyComplete("CSD_Kehj_Hell_ThroneOfHatred_Boss")
	-- We need a wait here because the death animation power also kicks off a
	-- camera reset ("Camera_Observer_normal") EG in the same tick.
	Hydra.Wait(0.1);
	
	local tPlayers = Hydra.QuestGetParticipants()
	
	for i, idNearbyPlayer in ipairs(tPlayers) do
		if Hydra.ActorGetWorld(idNearbyPlayer) == "CSD_Kehj_Hell_ThroneOfHatred" then
			Hydra.ActorPlayConversation(Conv_Lilith_Defeated_RTC, idNearbyPlayer)
		end
	end

	
end

function Start(idActorNPC, sConversation, idActorPlayer)
	------------------------------------------------------
	-- First Time Rewards
	
	local tAllPlayers = Hydra.QuestGetParticipants()
	
	for i, idPlayer in ipairs(tAllPlayers) do
		-- Drop the TreasureClass, which contains both "always" and "first time" rewards
		-- The First Time stuff is conditioned by the flag that is set after the dorp occurs
		-- idFirstTimeRewardLocation is set/created on "Actor Killed"
		Hydra.TreasureClassDropAtActorForPlayer(idFirstTimeRewardLocation, "FirstTimeReward_Campaign_Lilith", idPlayer)
		
		-- Set the variable, to mark that this player has recieved a reward
		Hydra.SetPlayerVariableFlag(idPlayer, "FirstTimeReward_Campaign_Lilith")
	end
	
	-- Since this boss doesn't have its own treasure class, also drop generic treasure at this time
	Hydra.TreasureClassDropAtActor(idFirstTimeRewardLocation, "Campaign_Boss")
	
	-- Remove the Reward Actor
	Hydra.ActorDelete(idFirstTimeRewardLocation)
	------------------------------------------------------
	
	
	
	Hydra.SetPlayerVariableFlag(idActorPlayer, "QST_Hell_Lilith_Killed")
	
end

	end

	Hydra.EventSend("MephistoSpotted")
